analysis.detail: Silk lists a finding affecting the semver npm package for mongosh. This is a false positive originating in the scanning tooling: While we do use semver as a transitive dependency of our build tooling (where it operates exclusively on trusted input), neither our shipped product nor the SBOM generated for it includes vulnerable versions of the package.

The augmented SBOM lists erroneous findings pointing to the tar package included in mongosh. These findings refer to the GNU tar command line utility, which we do not include in our shipped product, rather than the npm tar package which we do include, and are therefore a false positive originating in our scanning tooling.
